Building and installing vp
==========================

vp builds with either CMake (preferred) or autotools. Both produce the
same binary and install the same files; use whichever you like.

Requirements
------------

  - a C11 compiler (gcc or clang)
  - SDL2 and SDL2_image, with development headers
  - pkg-config
  - CMake >= 3.10 for the CMake path; nothing extra for the autotools
    path when building from a release tarball (configure is shipped)
  - optional: OpenSSL >= 1.1 for https support. Without it, vp still
    builds and http still works; https URLs report as unsupported.
  - optional: X11 headers (fullscreen/windowing extras on X)

Per-platform, that means roughly:

  Debian/Ubuntu:  apt install build-essential pkg-config \
                      libsdl2-dev libsdl2-image-dev libssl-dev
  Fedora/RHEL:    dnf install gcc pkg-config SDL2-devel \
                      SDL2_image-devel openssl-devel
                  (RHEL-family needs EPEL and CRB/PowerTools enabled;
                  SDL2 lives in CRB, SDL2_image in EPEL)
  FreeBSD:        pkg install cmake pkgconf sdl2 sdl2_image
                  (base system OpenSSL is found automatically)
  macOS:          brew install sdl2 sdl2_image pkg-config openssl@3

Building with CMake
-------------------

    cmake -B build
    cmake --build build
    ./build/src/vp <image files>

Install (default prefix /usr/local):

    cmake --install build              # may need sudo

Useful knobs:

    -DWITH_SSL=OFF                     # drop https support
    -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/opt/vp     # install elsewhere
    -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release

On macOS, OpenSSL is keg-only; if CMake misses it:

    OPENSSL_ROOT_DIR="$(brew --prefix openssl@3)" cmake -B build

Building with autotools
-----------------------

From a release tarball:

    ./configure
    make
    make install                       # may need sudo

From a git checkout (needs autoconf + automake):

    autoreconf -fi
    ./configure
    make

Useful knobs:

    --without-ssl                      # drop https support
    --prefix=/opt/vp                   # install elsewhere

VPATH builds work: mkdir build-ac && cd build-ac && ../configure && make

Testing
-------

The network test suite exercises the http/https fetch path against a
local server (never the real network). It needs python3 and the openssl
command-line tool:

    sh tests/net-tests.sh <path-to-vp-binary>

15 checks on an OpenSSL build, 12 without; the ipv6 check is skipped on
hosts without a ::1 loopback.

Packages
--------

    rpm:  rpmbuild -ta vp-<version>.tar.gz
    deb:  dpkg-buildpackage -b -us -uc     (from the unpacked tarball)

Prebuilt packages target the OpenSSL-3 era (RHEL/Rocky 9+, Fedora 36+,
Ubuntu 22.04+, Debian 12+). Older distros build fine from source
against their system OpenSSL 1.1, or with ssl disabled.
